Subject: [PATCH] Strip TBS dvb-core extensions

TBS extends struct dvb_frontend_ops with several callbacks in their own
kernel fork that don't exist in mainline:

  - .spi_read / .spi_write       raw FPGA register access
  - .eeprom_read / .eeprom_write    EEPROM access
  - .mcu_read / .mcu_write       MCU register access
  - .reg_i2cread / .reg_i2cwrite    raw I²C access
  - .read_temp                   chip temperature
  - .set_property                custom DTV property setters

Out-of-tree builds against mainline headers fail with:

    error: 'struct dvb_frontend_ops' has no member named 'spi_read'
    error: invalid use of undefined type 'struct ecp3_info'

Some of these (.spi_read, .spi_write, .eeprom_*, .mcu_*, .reg_i2c*)
also use TBS-specific argument struct types (struct ecp3_info, struct
eeprom_info, struct mcu24cxx_info, struct usbi2c_access) that aren't
in mainline either.

This patch:
  - Comments out all such callback assignments in dvb_frontend_ops
    initialisers across affected files.
  - Wraps the corresponding function definitions whose signatures
    reference TBS-only struct types in #if 0 ... #endif so they're
    not compiled. Handles both single-line and multi-line signatures.
  - Leaves .read_temp / .set_property function definitions intact
    (their signatures use mainline-compatible types), only commenting
    out the struct field assignments since the fields don't exist in
    mainline dvb_frontend_ops.

These callbacks expose raw FPGA-register / EEPROM access via custom
ioctls used by TBS-aware userspace tools — none are needed for normal
DVB tuning operation.
---
diff --git a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6882.c b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6882.c
index e58e290..135ab8f 100644
--- a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6882.c
+++ b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6882.c
@@ -1392,7 +1392,7 @@ static struct dvb_frontend_ops avl6882_ops = {
 	.get_frontend_algo		= avl6882fe_algo,
 	.tune				= avl6882_tune,
 
-	.set_property			= avl6882_set_property,
+	// .set_property			= avl6882_set_property,
 	.set_frontend			= avl6882_set_frontend,
 	.get_frontend = avl6882_get_frontend,
 };
